Rationale: Broadcom is currently worth over $800 on a DCF basis, and more like over ~$1200 if it were stretched on the valuation/in line with other stocks.  I know that puts the price off the charts technically and is laughably high, but it is what it is.  I have no idea why its trading where it is.  Usually there is an issue with the stock but its really a straightforward business with a large moat and is universally recommended by analysis's on the street.  The cash flow growth is 11% on average and the dividend yield is almost 5% right now.  Its trading at historically low RSI levels on the monthly (this is where it was before it rocketed 300% the last time around).  

&amp;nbsp;

With that said, this is my set up.  A 2 year time horizon to see this rocket and a short term put hedge to get us through this virus situation (no idea if further impact will be worth the option but just like to limit volatility on uncertain events).  Taking a chance here and hoping it pays off down the line.

